definition: (of a check etc) to cash/to honor a commitment
to cash/to exchange/to add (liquid)/to blend/one of the Eight Trigrams 八卦[ba1 gua4], symbolizing swamp/☱

sentences.english: At the very least, that will make it hard for a future President to keep tax-cut promises.
sentences.chinese: 不管怎样，下一任总统将很难兑现他们减税的承诺。

sentences.english: Can i please cash a check here?
sentences.chinese: 你能给我兑现一些旅行支票吗？

sentences.english: Gains are realized when assets are liquidated to cash.
sentences.chinese: 当资产进行清算兑现后，收益得以实现。

sentences.english: He went to bank to encash a draft.
sentences.chinese: 他去银行兑现一张汇票。

sentences.english: Eventually, perhaps soon, the market must obey Mr Micawber’s dictum.
sentences.chinese: 最终，也许很快，市场肯定会兑现米考伯的格言。

sentences.english: Can I have this money order cashed?
sentences.chinese: 我可以在这里兑现这张汇票吗？

sentences.english: Bill will promise you the moon, but he won't live up to his promises.
sentences.chinese: 比尔会为你夸下海口，但他是不会兑现承诺的。

sentences.english: However ANZ is expected to battle bigger and cashed-up competitors for the assets.
sentences.chinese: 但是澳新银行预计战斗更大，兑现后续竞争者的资产。

sentences.english: The problem with doomsday investing is that it's difficult to cash out.
sentences.chinese: 世界末日投资的问题在于很难兑现。

sentences.english: I need a fifty-dollar postal order, please.
sentences.chinese: 你能替我兑现这张邮政汇票吗？
它是一张美国限时兑现卡。

sentences.english: Panics tend to be short-lived, offering a brief opportunity to cash in.
sentences.chinese: 恐慌一般是短期的，提供了兑现利润的机会。

sentences.english: The President promised a $50 rebate for each taxpayer but failed to deliver it.
sentences.chinese: 总统曾答应让每个纳税人减税50美元，但未能兑现。

sentences.english: That means an investor rush to redeem the bonds could delay payment.
sentences.chinese: 这意味着一位投资者急于兑现可能会导致付款推迟。

sentences.english: Can I have this money order cashed?
sentences.chinese: 我可以在这儿兑现汇款单吗？

sentences.english: Can I have this money order cashed, please?
sentences.chinese: 请问可不可以把这张汇款单兑现？

definition: to promise/to undertake to do something/commitment
to fulfill (one's obligations)/to carry out (a task)/to implement (an agreement)/to perform
achievement/accomplishment/(in more recent usage) performance (of a business, employee etc)/results
to fall due (loan etc)/to expire (visa etc)/to mature (investment bond etc)
